The image shows a screenshot of an online survey form with various fields. Here is the JSON array representation of the actions required to complete the survey:

```json
[
  {"tool":"fill","key":"age","value":18},
  {"tool":"select","key":"follow_by_age","value":"very_closely"},
  {"tool":"select","key":"employment_status","value":"student"},
  {"tool":"set_range","key":"watch_time","value":5.0},
  {"tool":"click","key":"next"}
]
```

Please note that the "fill" action for the age field is set to 18, which is the minimum age allowed in the survey. The other actions are as described: selecting "very_closely" from the dropdown for the follow_by_age question, selecting "student" from the employment_status dropdown, setting the watch_time slider to 5 hours per day, and clicking on the "Next" button after filling out the age field.

The JSON array does not include any actions for the remaining fields such as trust_coverage, mood_impact, country_satisfaction, future_interest, favorite_moment, or the survey instructions. These fields are likely to be filled in with responses based on the user's answers to the questions and are not part of the automated action sequence described by the JSON array.
